║   KEY FINDING: MODEL 1 (BASIC HAWKES) ANALYSIS               ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

Model 1 specification:
  λ(t) = μ(background) + α·exp(-β·Δt)
  where α is CONSTANT (no mark dependence)

RESULT: Model 1 converged to α ≈ 0
  • Base triggering: α = 0.0000 (essentially zero)
  • Log-likelihood: -79441.39 
  • Better than Poisson, worse than Model 2

INTERPRETATION:
  The optimizer chose minimal triggering effect, suggesting that
  a UNIFORM triggering rate does not adequately capture protest
  contagion. Instead, the data require HETEROGENEOUS triggering
  where different protest types have different contagion effects.

